# Per-Dockerfile ignore (BuildKit). Applied when building with
# `-f apps/web/Dockerfile`. Takes precedence over the root .dockerignore.

# Workspace members not needed for the web image. The Dockerfile only
# COPYs the web + types package.json files, so the rest never reaches the
# build context — but explicit exclusion keeps the context smaller and
# guards against accidental future COPYs.
apps/api
# Exclude packages/cli wholesale, but keep its package.json — the homepage
# imports the CLI version from there for the "CLI vX.Y.Z now available" banner.
packages/cli/*
!packages/cli/package.json
packages/create-ruleshub
packages/ruleshub-kit

# Caches and local clutter
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.log

# Repo metadata
.git
.github
**/CLAUDE.md
**/README.md
**/audit.md
**/Dockerfile*

# Local env files — never bake into images
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
